snippet.textDisplay:
@Shung Wang What's saving do?? If you were to bury your money in your backyard , 2yrs later , its still gonna be the same amount . However ; If you were to wait 10 yrs to dig it up , the dollar amount wouldn't change , cause its been buried for a decade. Unfornately when it comes to the dollar's actual value . It wouldnt be worth as much as it was 10 yrs ago.. Regarding my orignal question ( what's saving do ?)
Well saving is you working very hard for your money and slowly trying to make it grow. The frame of mind you should have when it comes to investing, is to hurry up and get started , and make your money work for you ! Its pointless saving up to invest .. Rather it's Crypto, SP-500,Nasdaq, Dow jones , there are plenty of mutual /index funds etc where you can purchase as little as $5 , so my point is , you don't need a lot to get started.
